data.title: Wiz Khalifa Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Wiz Khalifa with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Started rapping at 9 years old

At age 16, his mom took him to get his first tattoo

Stage name originated from his nickname Wiz, short for wisdom and his Muslim grandfather added Khalifa which means"successor" in Arabic

Founded Taylor Gang records, an independent record label

His first number one single, "Black and Yellow," refers to the city colors of Pittsburgh

Named Rookie of the Year by Source Magazine and was featured on the December 2010 cover

Pittsburgh City Council declared December 12, 2012 Whiz Khalifa day in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania

Donated 1,700 back packs to students at his alma mater, Taylor Allerdice High School and other district students in September 2015

His 2015 single, with Charlie Puth, "See You Again" was number one on the Billboard Hot 100 list for 12 non-consecutive weeks
